{
  "stem": "7598.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You asked me about where we returned to live to and how I felt about my parents.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we went to live in my uncle's flat with them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at that point, it never occurred to me that my parents could be anywhere else but in France.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And having worked out that they crossed the frontier afterwards, my brother and I felt sure that they were also caught by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we waited desperately for them to come back, and I used to wait at the end of a tram line every night to see whether my parents were on the, on the tram or not.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 13-- yep.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] At one stage, before we were caught by the Germans, we had the opportunity near [NON-ENGLISH] to catch a, catch a boat which would take refugees to England.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle and aunt and everybody was very keen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think this is, this is the-- I know it's true, but I'm saying, well, whether I was the greatest influence, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember refusing point blank to go on that ship.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, my parents are going to go to Cognac, and I'm not going to England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't get on the ship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Exactly why, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I know that I was very relieved.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Ironically, my parents, after having begged and borrowed and managed to walk across to practically Calais, by the time they had no soles on their shoes, found a Polish ship which was meant to go to Bordeaux and then along the coast of Spain and Portugal.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And because my father still spoke Polish or because they heard his sad tale of the children, they allowed him onto the ship.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
